The Beijing 2022 Winter Olympic and Paralympic Games test events are halfway through, and all preparations are ready at present, an official said at a news conference on Friday. The Beijing 2022 Winter Olympic Games is scheduled to begin on February 4 and end on February 20. The Winter Paralympic Games is scheduled to begin on March 4 and end on March 13. Ten international events, three international training weeks and two domestic testing sessions have been scheduled to take place from October 5 to the end of year. The events in December are the Nordic Biathlon Intercontinental Cup, Ski Jumping Intercontinental Cup, and the Biathlon International Training Week.